To whom it may concern:

Make it leave my brain, lest I stab some shit.
Let me grow a pair, lest I lose all control.
Make me a little less emo, lest I become totally pathetic.

kthx.

So here's the thing. I am an extremely sarcastic person. I also don't deal with uncomfortable situations well. I either laugh loudly, to break the mood, or I stare at my feet and pretend I'm not listening, when I still am. And I always give advice when no one wants it. Therefore, I am always worried that what I do offends people. I mean, ALWAYS worried. Not just a little either. It's why I don't have a lot of relationships, why I'm the plucky comic relief, and why even now, I sit here typing, alone. I don't want to be alone anymore. But it seems to me that there is no other way at this point, because I can't read people, especially in uncomfortable situations. Maybe I am just...you know, it doesn't matter. It really doesn't. I'm done.

So I'm totally lame. I won't tell you why, because it is, in fact, entirely TOO lame...but there you are.

Lame to the point of nauseousness, in fact.

Moving on.

I still don't have a schedule, band camp is going to kill me, and work is work.

Back to the nauseousness?

I really love this new job. Except the occasional shmuck of a kid, they're really smart and fun to work with. w00t.

The fireworks were sooooooooooooo much better this year. Erin liked the sparkly ones.

My feet hurt.

Also quite tired I am. (It makes me use the force.)

This is a pointless entry.

Ha.

I don't want to go to symphonyyyyyyyyyyyyy.

Don't make me.

When you take an online exam, and you realize about two-thirds of the way through that you really need to poop.

Not fun.

They were so good, I almost felt bad eating them.




Almost.

So I had two exams today. The first was in psychology, and it only took 20 minutes. I was like, wtf mate? But whatever. That means I'm done with that class forever. FOR-EV-UR. Oh yes. The other exam was in German. It took me an hour, and I was the second one done. I'm willing to bet a lot of them were there til the end. But, I got all excited because there was one section we had to read and respond to, which was a page long...and I understood every word of it! Go me. It was about the guy that voices the Harry Potter books on tape. He did over 100 voices for them. I was like WOW. But yeah...I should have taken it with me, it was interesting.

Two more exams...I'm almost done.

Peace.


pee ess - I love this song a lot.

So now I'm accepted into the music department. Dr. Cole called my house and sent me an email. They shouldn't be allowed to fuck with my emotions like that.

I'm gonna do it.

I have an exam in two hours. I'm not really studying for it. At this point, I either know it or I don't. So...blah.

I'm out of here Friday. I'm out of here Friday. I'm out...

So let's get raunchy tonight...and go see American Dreamz. God, that movie was so good. I haven't laughed like that in so long. You have been Omerized.

Oh, and this little detail...

HAPPY BIRTHDAY COLLEEN!


that is all.

October 22nd:

3 neat facts
1797 - One thousand meters (3,200 feet) above Paris, Andre-Jacques Garnerin makes the first recorded parachute jump.
1878 - The first rugby match under floodlights takes place in Salford, between Broughton and Swinton.
1976 - Red Dye No. 4 is banned by the US Food and Drug Administration after it is discovered that it causes tumors in the bladders of dogs. The dye is still used in Canada.

Well that was fun.

You know, I don't know what to tell you. How to you live with yourselves? To disrespect? To lie? To disregard? To cave? To lead on? To cheat? To badmouth? TO HATE? I cannot see it. They are your blood, or the people you love, or the people you care for. Funny way of showing it. I'm sick of it. Is it Redford? Maybe. It's my family, it's my friends, it's my "friends", it's the guy that's the friend-of-a-friend's cousin twice-removed, it's these PEOPLE. What are you trying to prove? Oh yeah, you're a real tough guy. You showed them, with your equally hateful and terrible ways. One huge struggle to out-do one another's bad deed. Oh, yeah, way to be the nice guy, leading people on, lying to them, disregarding them, playing games. Yes, you, in your infinite wisdom, have a right to judge my life, or their life. It really helps the situation, too, when you won't TALK to the person, you hide yourself away, lock yourself in your room, assume superiority. We live TOGETHER,  we develop RELATIONSHIPS, for what? To just ignore them? Yes, it's YOUR life, fuck the world! NO. FUCK YOU.

And business is boomin'! I'm open for business!

Yeah, well I'm gonna expand your business!




I'm done.

My stomach hurts (too much hummus) and I can't breathe with no inhaler and I have allergy problems...nicht gut. Borderline miserable, in fact.

I went to group career advising today. Turns out if you major in German teaching you can minor in history, teach history and German, AND still get a job in Michigan. And, if after you student teach you take a 6-week spring course, you're K-12 certified and employers love you. I'm excited about this...should work out. I will have to study in Duesseldorf though, not sure how I feel about taking a plane that long, being miserable...I mean, I couldn't even handle the trip to and from DC, and that was an hour. :-/

Long day.

Bis spaeter, meine Freunden.

Why is it that I can barely keep my eyes open all day, and then when it's two in the morning I'm still awake?

L A M E .

Woke up at 8:30.
Showered, blow-dryed, brushed.
Class.
Lunch.
Class.
Class.
Class.
45 minute break.
Award dealy. (GROOOOOOOOOOOOOAAAAAAAAAAAAAAANNNNNN)
Dinner with Mom.
Class.
DONE.

My stomach HURTS...out of nowhere! Damn it!

My mom told me she is for sure fixing the van, and it's being towed tomorrow. Love to her.

Last night at 12:30 the power went out in all of the residence halls (except the Towers) and some of the buildings. Apparently there was a down wire. As soon as it went out, these girls in my wing started screaming down the hall. I was like, yes, it is fact: you're morons. A girl in the other wing told me her neighbors across the hall started screaming aout terrorism, packed up a bunch of shit, and left. I was like WOW. Amazing. As my battery was full, I spent the time playing this Tetris game I found online for free. That game sucks. Once you get to a certain point scorewise, it says OVERLOAD and closes. And, Tetris is my GAME, so, of course, I keep getting over 900,000 with like 400 lines and it's like "No, fuck you." DAMN.

I feel a WOO coming on Cuz, a couple WOOs coming on Cuz, WOO! WOO! There they was...

I have homework. Lots and lots of homework. I also have to do all of my German tonight, because I have to go to some award ceremony tomorrow during my normal German homework time. Again, DAMN.

Figures NOW is the time I feel ready to vomit. DAMN DAMN DAMN.

Peace out.

You are not black.

Love, Mary.

Hello. It's been awhile. Anyhoo. Had the surgery, and I'm feeling good. I'm supposed to go back to school on Monday. Yay for me. I haven't had any problems, and the surgery, basically, could not have gone better. Thought I'd check in and say "HI".

Peace out.

So, today in physics, my teacher was discussing exactly what X-Rays are. (We're doing the light spectrum.) He was explaining E=mc2, saying that mass times the speed of light squared equals the amount of energy. Ok. So, he mentioned the atom bomb...you know, the one that hit Hiroshima during WWII? Well, that had the mass of a Post-It note, and yet it vaporized an entire city block where it hit, destroyed the city, and its radioactive remnants are still causing leukemia and the like. Then he said, "Now, imagine this bomb that we created in the 40's if it had one kilogram of mass. That's what we make now. It would vaporize Ypsilanti."

Makes you think...

Welp, this has happened to me twice now, so thought I'd give you a head's up...

[Courtney's Name]:  I found your picture: http://208.187.190.34/~vcc/Image_18.com
[Me]: what?
[Me]: huh?
[Me]: what is it?

It's an AIM virus. This happened with my cousin once too: the virus maker sends you a message as someone on your list, and convince you to download a file. Usually, it begins a new conversation. If they don't respond, it's not them. (FYI: The file was a MS DOS file, not a picture. I mean, obviously it's not a pic, it's a virus, but make sure you look at what kind of file it is...)

http://www.siena.edu/antivirus/viruses/AIMviruses.asp <---Has a little more information.

Hmm...it just happened again, once I closed the window...that's weird...

Anyway, that's all.

So, I hauled Basey up that hill, and nearly died, but it was ok. My chest still hurts, but it hurt just walking up the hill for German. I suppose the two Thanksgivings and the overexposure to cats did me in...

I had said last week (well, two weeks ago) that I did NOT want to do my physics presentation after these two music majors, Amy and Chris, who were going to duet on trombone and french horn. They're seniors, and I was like, "Dude, haven't played in months!!" Amy's last name starts with A, so they went first. And did really well. They pretty much said everything I could have said. As a side note, Amy's trombone is GORGEOOOOUUUUUS. It's like, twice as nice as Kyle's jazz horn, and THAT was about $3000, I think he said. Dang.

Anyway, right after they go, Jesse goes, "Ms. DeLong." Cock-juggling thunder cunt! [heh, see Blade Trinity] So, I go up there, and I played a really simple version of Russian Sailor's Dance and just reitterated what they had already said. So, I get done, and Chris goes, "Why aren't you in band?" I explained my dilemma, and he's like, "You can try out for Symphonic Band at the beginning of the semester. I'll take you to Boerma, he'll give you correct information..." So, my lab partner, Amy, Chris and I walked over to Alexander, and I met this guy. He seems cool. Apparently, the try-out information will be posted in a week and a half or two weeks, right before finals start. And, my lab partner, Sam, had stopped playing her oboe, but she decided she wants to play again, so she's going to go with me to sign up. I guess they take everyone, so I'm not nervous. Plus, Chris and Amy seemed really impressed, just by that little bit I played. I just want to play. I'm excited that I'll get to again.

On another note, I said I was going to take a nap, but I might wait a little bit. I'm still tired, but...I don't know. Now I'm not AS tired, because I'm in a good mood. I guess.

Anyway, peace out.

I do not want to hike up that fucking hill with Basey. Not at all. But, I have to for physics. "Present some sort of example of physics in the arts." Bitches.

When I get back, I'm totally taking a nap. Totally.

Anyway, make a decision, and leave me a comment.plz.kthx.

I don't know how many of you watch wrestling, or ever did. But, as Sean informed me yesterday, Eddie Guererro was found dead Sunday in his hotel room. Now, I'm not gonna lie: I never liked Eddie's wrestling character. But, I'm watching RAW right now, which is a tribute to Eddie. And it's one of the saddest things I've ever seen. You don't see Chris Benoit cry. You don't see Triple H cry. You don't see 7'2" Paul Wight cry. It doesn't happen. But, it is now. Booker T, Kurt Angle, Rey Mysterio...seeing them cry is sooo depressing.

Hahaha...they just showed a clip of Eddie spraying the Big Show with semen...that's awesome.

Anyway, I should be doing my speech. I started it, but I still have some stuff to do.

See ya.

Edit--Damn it, now Batista's crying. :*(
